dismissalComment.html: run out, Masakadza's fun stops here, Rasel changes the pace and Masakadza gets forward and angles it down to short third man, no realistic chance of a single but the batsman sets off, there's confusion in the calling and he turns around and makes a desperate attempt to make his ground, Ashraful fires the throw to Mushfiqur and the third umpire confirms the run out

commentTextItems.html: all over, tossed up on the off, waits for it, takes on a length and smashes it over the bowler's head to seal a 4-1 win

commentPostTextItems.html: Bangladesh have done it comfortably. They were chasing a fairly low target, despite the resistance offered by Brendan Taylor and Ray Price, and were guided superbly by Mushfiqur who played a calm innings but deprived himself of a deserving century. However, if one were to pick the player of the day, it would have to be Dolar Mahmud, who rocked Zimbabwe with four wickets to help restrict them to an easily chaseable score. Bangladesh have won three ODI series in a row and have signed off from this series with authority. Shakib's captaincy has been hugely impressive and more importantly, he's led by example, both here and in the tour of West Indies. One shouldn't be too surprised if Bangladesh persist with him as their captain once Mortaza returns. We'll get you the presentation details in a bit.

Utseya: "Yes, we are disappointed but Bangladesh proved they were the better team. The younger players have done well. We thank the crowd for supporting us and we hope to put in a better performance next time. With the franchise system coming in, it can only get better."

Shakib: "The boys have been showing their character, have been performing well throughout this series and  have played very good cricket. The players have stepped up and Mushfiqur played well today. The top order has clicked. I'm focusing on my game, and the boys have supported me well."
Dolar Mahmud is the Man of the Match.
Dolar: "It's good to perform well in international cricket and I played well this time. The wicket was providing assistance and I made use of it."
Tamim is the Man of the series with 300-odd runs, including that match-winning 150-odd in the fourth ODI.

Tamim: "This is my first such award and hopefully there'll be more to come. The 154 was my best innings and hopefully there'll be many more. The top order played very well this series, and Junaid supported me really well. The boys have performed superbly and we're very happy."

That's all from us, folks. Thanks for tuning in and sending us your feedback. It's been a pleasure bringing you this series and we hope you've enjoyed it. Until the next time, on behalf of everyone at Cricinfo, this is Sid Talya signing off. Adios!

commentPostTextItems.html: He deserved a century, did Mushfiqur. Did all the hard work, stuck it out for 45 overs, taking the singles, two's and striking the timely boundaries. He was promoted up the order and lived up to the expectations but a rush of blood in the dying stages of the game has cost him a century

headshotImage.longCaption: Charles Coventry player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Charles Coventry player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Charles Coventry player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Charles Coventry c †Mushfiqur Rahim b Dolar Mahmud 0 (7b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Coventry's gone! The swing's doing the trick for Mahmud, pitched up outside off, had frustrated Coventry so far and the batsman went for flowing drive through mid-off, it moved away to kiss the outside edge and Mushfiqur hurled himself to his right to snap a sharp one, the record-holder's been dismissed for a duck

headshotImage.caption: Syed Rasel player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Syed Rasel player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Mohammad Ashraful player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mohammad Ashraful player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza run out (†Mushfiqur Rahim/Mohammad Ashraful) 25 (24b 4x4 0x6 37m) SR: 104.16

dismissalComment.html: run out, Masakadza's fun stops here, Rasel changes the pace and Masakadza gets forward and angles it down to short third man, no realistic chance of a single but the batsman sets off, there's confusion in the calling and he turns around and makes a desperate attempt to make his ground, Ashraful fires the throw to Mushfiqur and the third umpire confirms the run out

dismissalText.commentary: Malcolm Waller b Dolar Mahmud 10 (12b 1x4 0x6 25m) SR: 83.33

dismissalComment.html: timber! Superb delivery, the inswinger this time. Pitched on a good length outside off and Waller reached forward to defend it into the off side, it darted back in to beat him through the gate and crash into the stumps, Zimbabwe are sliding here

headshotImage.caption: Syed Rasel player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Syed Rasel player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Sean Williams lbw b Syed Rasel 12 (13b 2x4 0x6) SR: 92.3

dismissalComment.html: gone! Rasel's struck, Williams goes, the inswinger, short of a good length outside off and cut back in sharply, Williams rocked back to punch it towards mid-on but was done in by the movement, was rapped on the pads in front of the off stump, the umpire had no hesitation and he's made the right call

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura lbw b Dolar Mahmud 12 (18b 2x4 0x6) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: Dolar gets his fourth! Angling in towards middle from slightly wide of the crease, came half-forward and tried to close the face with bat perilously close to his pads to play it into the leg side, missed and was struck plumb in front

dismissalText.commentary: Prosper Utseya b Mahmudullah 21 (39b 3x4 0x6 46m) SR: 53.84

dismissalComment.html: bowled'im! Poor shot, that. Tossed up, lands on a good length on middle and spins in sharply towards leg, goes for the pull when the shot wasn't really on, misses and is bowled.

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor lbw b Mehrab Hossain jnr 61 (86b 3x4 1x6 97m) SR: 70.93

dismissalComment.html: bowled flat from round the wicket, angled it in towards off stump and it spun away, Taylor went for the sweep, looking to play it through square leg but missed, was rapped on the pads and was given. Replays show it would have missed off, and he was struck outside the line, poor call

headshotImage.caption: Naeem Islam player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Naeem Islam player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Graeme Cremer st †Mushfiqur Rahim b Naeem Islam 10 (11b 1x4 0x6 13m) SR: 90.9

dismissalComment.html: stumped, comes round the wicket, fires it short outside off as he sees Cremer charging down, tries to slap it through cover, misses and Mushfiqur takes off the bails to find him well short

dismissalText.commentary: Ray Price lbw b Syed Rasel 46 (58b 4x4 1x6 70m) SR: 79.31

dismissalComment.html: moved well across to scoop it over short fine again but was rapped on the pads, Sahiba gave him out but he actually wasn't as it struck him outside the line and would have missed off anyway, poor decision again

image.caption: Ray Price
image.longCaption: Ray Price portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

dismissalText.commentary: Tamim Iqbal b Price 4 (23b 0x4 0x6 45m) SR: 17.39

dismissalComment.html: strikes immediately! A lot of turn there for him, short outside off, spun back in sharply, Tamim rocked back to attempt the cut, missed it completely and was bowled

dismissalText.commentary: Mushfiqur Rahim st †Coventry b Price 98 (121b 11x4 0x6 185m) SR: 80.99

dismissalComment.html: he misses out on a century! stumped, tossed it up outside off, Mushfiqur wanted to get it over and done with, charged out of his crease to loft it over the bowler's head, it turned away and Coventry clipped the bails to find him agonizingly short of a maiden ODI ton

headshotImage.longCaption: Mohammad Ashraful player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Ashraful c Sibanda b Chigumbura 4 (7b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 57.14

dismissalComment.html: what a catch! An absolute stunner, bowled short and wide, goes for the cut, connects well but finds Sibanda at point who times his jump to perfection and plucks it out of thin air one-handed, tumbles but holds on, two down now

dismissalText.commentary: Raqibul Hasan c Waller b Utseya 24 (48b 3x4 0x6 48m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: Raqibul departs, the bowling change works! Tossed it up well outside off, reached for it with a bug lunge and tried to paddle it down, all that hard work would have yielded just a run but this is worse, it catches the top edge and Waller takes the easiest of catches at short fine

dismissalText.commentary: Shakib Al Hasan c Masakadza b Cremer 30 (40b 2x4 0x6 44m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: Shakib's holed out! Cremer gave it some air, it was pitched up outside off, Shakib came down the track and tried to clear long-on, got quite a bit of bat on it but didn't get the desired elevation, landed safe in the palms of Masakadza in the deep

dismissalText.commentary: Mahmudullah not out 27 (41b 1x4 1x6 47m) SR: 65.85

stories.title: Dolar and Mushfiqur make it 4-1
stories.subTitle: Zimbabwe v Bangladesh, 5th ODI, Bulawayo
stories.summary: An incisive opening spell from Dolar Mahmud rocked Zimbabwe, and though they recovered to post 210, it was easily chased down by Bangladesh thanks to Mushfiqur Rahim's 98
